  "text": "The LLVM IR-to-Machine-Code generation pipeline consists of several key stages:\n\n1. **Instruction Selection (SelectionDAGISel)**: The SelectionDAGISel class is defined in `llvm/include/llvm/CodeGen/SelectionDAGISel.h` (line 45). This is the common base class for SelectionDAG-based pattern-matching instruction selectors that convert LLVM IR to target-specific SelectionDAG nodes. The implementation is in `llvm/lib/CodeGen/SelectionDAG/SelectionDAGISel.cpp`.\n\n2. **DAG Construction (SelectionDAGBuilder)**: The SelectionDAGBuilder class is defined in `llvm/lib/CodeGen/SelectionDAG/SelectionDAGBuilder.h` (line 96). This class translates IR instructions into DAG nodes. The implementation is in `llvm/lib/CodeGen/SelectionDAG/SelectionDAGBuilder.cpp`.\n\n3. **Instruction Scheduling (ScheduleDAGRRList)**: The ScheduleDAGRRList class is defined in `llvm/lib/CodeGen/SelectionDAG/ScheduleDAGRRList.cpp` (line 138). This class implements instruction scheduling using a resource reservation list approach, inheriting from ScheduleDAGSDNodes.\n\n4. **Register Allocation (RAGreedy)**: The register allocation is implemented by the RAGreedy class, which is defined in `llvm/lib/CodeGen/RegAllocGreedy.h` (line 59). This is the greedy register allocator that performs register allocation. The implementation is in `llvm/lib/CodeGen/RegAllocGreedy.cpp`.\n\n5. **Machine-Level Function Representation (MachineFunction)**: The MachineFunction class is defined in `llvm/include/llvm/CodeGen/MachineFunction.h` (line 294). This class represents a function at the machine code level, containing a list of MachineBasicBlock instances and target-specific information about the generated code.\n\nAll these classes are part of the `llvm/lib/CodeGen/` subsystem which is responsible for lowering LLVM IR through various transformation passes to ultimately generate machine code."
}

